  E := V(G)
  Indep := fun S ↦ ∃ M, G.IsMatching M ∧ S ⊆ V(G, M)
  -- Axiom 1: The empty set is independent
  -- Axiom 2: If S is independent and T ⊆ S, then T is independent
  -- Axiom 3: If S and T are independent and |S| < |T|, then S ∪ {v} is independent for some v ∈ T \ S
```

We've defined the matchable sets as the independent sets of our matroid. Now we need to prove the three axioms.

