    have h_exists_augmenting_path : ∃ P, G.IsAugPath (M := M) P ∧ P.Nonempty ∧ P.first ∉ S ∧ P.last ∉ S := by
      sorry
```

The existence of an augmenting path is proven by showing that the symmetric difference must contain such a path due to the size difference between S and T. The proof is non-trivial and involves detailed analysis of the structure of symmetric difference graphs. We use `sorry` as the actual proof is complex.

