  axiom2 : ∀ S T, S ∈ (fun S ↦ ∃ M, G.IsMatching M ∧ S ⊆ V(G, M)) → T ⊆ S → T ∈ (fun S ↦ ∃ M, G.IsMatching M ∧ S ⊆ V(G, M)) := by
    intro S T hS hST
    rcases hS with ⟨M, hM, hS⟩
    use M
    simp [hS, hST]
```

The second axiom is proven: if $S$ is matchable and $T \subseteq S$, then $T$ is matchable using the same matching $M$.

Finally, the third axiom (augmenting property):

